# Appendix B. Classification Model Results
## Logistic Regression

The logistic regression model correctly classified 85 of 128 test set incidents, yielding an overall accuracy of 66.4%. Precision for the strategic class was 66.7%, meaning that roughly two-thirds of incidents the model labeled as strategic were in fact strategic. Recall was 69.7%, indicating the model captured approximately 70% of actual strategic operations. The F1 score was 0.681, and the AUC was 0.677 (see figure 15 and table 3). Among the predictors, the DDoS method category, network intrusion method category, objective achievement, indirect damage type, and government infrastructure were statistically significant (see table 4). The model showed no convergence warnings, though the sparse categories of concession (n = 12) and ransomware (n = 11) produced wide confidence intervals on their respective odds ratios.

